Title: Cloud Solutions for Communication Service Providers

Span.Text: “By reducing our IT spend by 15% through the use of Microsoft cloud services, we free up money to spend on creating new innovative services to make the business more competitive.”
Adrian Steel, Global Head of Infrastructure, Telefónica
Telefónica have implemented a hybrid cloud strategy that’s enabled them to trim IT costs by 15% and deliver far more reliable IT services to the business.

Microsoft System Center handles applications, component services, VMs, and VHDs across multiple cloud stacks and hyper-visors. System Center also addresses many of the emerging requirements of ETSI MANO Architecture.
The Microsoft Cloud OS stack integrates with higher level cloud resource managers. And by abstracting the infrastructure, it enables CSPs to seamlessly deploy Linux and Windows workloads.

Strategic business insights into customer analytics and risk exposure enable financial institutions to monetise data, generating higher revenues, improving customer service, providing stronger risk management and improved operational efficiency.

Azure ExpressRoute enables telco grade managed network services such as MPLS to establish highly secure vLAN connections between telco on-premises cloud based services and Azure hosted services and resources.

Microsoft enables Communication Service Provider’s (CSPs) to flexibly deploy and use technology in the way that makes the most sense for their business. With CSPs being a data-intensive industry, the cloud makes this easier using on-premise connected cloud platform for data centres.
